Business Brief -- Pittston Co.:
   Earnings Report Is Delayed
   Pending Action by FASB
The Stamford, Conn., company said it is unsure of the
effect on 1991 earnings of the adoption of the accounting
rule. It reported fourth-quarter 1990 earnings of $20
million, or 68 cents a share, on revenue of $490 million, and
full-year earnings of $61.1 million, or $1.64 a share, on
revenue of $1.85 billion.